  "text": "A total of 20 condensate and light oil samples were collected, analyzed and studied. In this paper we present and discuss geochemical data for two representative samples: a condensate from well Temane-13 and a light oil from well Inhassoro-9z. Geochemical measurements (API, sulfur, metals, and saturates, aromatic, resins, asphaltenes (SARA)) on these liquids, whole oil gas chromatography (WOGC) and biomarker (GC-MS) analyses were performed at Weatherford (Shenandoah, TX, USA) using methods and equipment described in [CITATION_1] .",
